rComments: She is VERY knowledgable about the field she just lacks social skills. She comes off mean in the classroom, but is quite nice when you interact 1 on 1 and VERY helpful. Her assignments are fair and so was her final. Read the book and take notes-this is a REAL university course not your typical HLT 'bird' course. Just know the basic concepts/ideas.

this teacher was not approachable in the classroom, it was not until I went to her office hours that she became helpful and really nice to me.  He finals are very specific and mostly based on the text book its only a hard exam if you did not read all the text book

Would not recommend her course.  She may be clear in her speech but that is not what constitutes teaching.  Teaching involves providing students with material in a way that can help them understand and remember.  No lecture slides offered, and her slides were cluttered & unorganized& Most importantly, what she spoke was not connected to the slides.
She nods her head a lot, don't know if anyone else noticed! But overall she is a great prof, her lecture notes are hard to study. you gotta really think about the material.

Great Professor! Incredibly knowledgable and crystal clear in her teachings.  She is a bit unapproachable and rude at times but if you actually have something inteligent and new to contribute to the class disscussion she welcomes your opinion.  Be warned the exam is quite random and not easy, the highest mark on the exam for Fall 2010 was 79%.

This prof is very informed in her field. Her lectures are extremely helpful & she conveys the info so well. Her papers are also great to write. I really enjoyed the topics addressed for the papers. Will definitely take her courses again in the future.
She's very informative but i was extremely afraid to ask her any questions b/c whenever students would ask her questions, her reply would almost be like she is attacking them.
